{"questionId":"15421","questionHtml":"<p>Find the equation of the regression line of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> on <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 15.5x - 80\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>15.5</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>80</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong><em>(A1)</em><em>&nbsp; (C2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"15.5x\">\n  <mn>15.5</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for −80. Award at most <em><strong>(A1)(A0)</strong></em> if answer is not an equation. Award <em><strong>(A0)(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = - 80x + 15.5\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>80</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>15.5</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"15421","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.T_2a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the equation of the regression line of y on x .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}